[DQR.IFRS.0126.9595] The statement 13 - Rapport över kassaflöden includes an inconsistent calculation. The value of the concept ifrs-full:CashFlowsFromUsedInFinancingActivities of -1,338,000,000 should be equal to the sum of its child components defined in the calculation linkbase. The sum of these child components is -470,000,000. The values of the addends is determined by adding the values of the child concepts with a decimal value of -6. All values in the financial statements should use the same decimal value. The values reported in the financial statement in the current reporting period of 2021-01-01 to 2021-12-31 should be complete if the financial statement is to be mathematically accurate and complete. The components of ifrs-full:CashFlowsFromUsedInFinancingActivities that should add to -1,338,000,000 are comprised of the following:
- DividendsPaidToNoncontrollingInterestsClassifiedAsFinancingActivities 1,417,000,000 + OtherInflowsOutflowsOfCashClassifiedAsFinancingActivities -3,000,000 - PaymentsOfLeaseLiabilitiesClassifiedAsFinancingActivities 121,000,000 + ProceedsFromBorrowingsClassifiedAsFinancingActivities 5,150,000,000 - RepaymentsOfBorrowingsClassifiedAsFinancingActivities 3,700,000,000 - RepaymentsOfCurrentBorrowings 379,000,000
The addends are calculated based on the calculation linkbase defined for 13 - Rapport över kassaflöden. If addends are missing then the calculation tree should be amended. The rule will not add dimension components as the financial statement does not include a table. If dimensions are used on the statement then add a table to ensure that the dimensions are defined correctly.
